# AGE Runway — Premium Site Design Brief

## Brand & product

- **Name:** AGE Runway (Runway)
- **Company:** Anderson Global Enterprises (AGE)
- **Audience:** B2B operators — roofing owners, local service founders, expert creators
- **Product:** Done-for-you AI content pipeline (voice → script → video → publish)
- **Vibe:** Premium ops tool — Stripe, Linear, Vercel — not AI gimmick sites

## Visual direction

- Clean, minimalist, confident. No AI slop (neon blobs, particles, robot imagery).
- **Colors:** Charcoal base (`--bg-base`), one primary accent (blue `#3B82F6`), one supporting accent (teal `#14B8A6`), used sparingly.
- **Typography:** Space Grotesk headings, Inter body. Precise, calm, confident.
- **Layout:** Grid-based, generous spacing, distinct section panels, subtle hover states only.
- **Imagery:** Abstract pipeline diagrams, modular cards, system flows — not generic AI art.

## Pages

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `index.html` | Primary marketing landing |
| `runway-pricing.html` | 3-tier pricing + checkout form |
| `runway-login.html` | Portal login |
| `runway-forgot.html` | Password reset |
| `runway-dashboard.html` | Flight Deck (authenticated) |
| `runway-success.html` | Post-checkout welcome |
| `css/runway.css` | Shared design system |
| `js/runway.js` | Shared interactions |

## Anti-patterns

- No over-decorated gradients, spinning globes, or blurry blobs
- No merging Talksmith Studio styling into Runway
- Portal = client-facing; ops tooling stays internal
- Copy: confident B2B SaaS tone, not consumer AI hype

## Definition of done

- Matches flight-deck visual system across marketing + portal
- Desktop-first, graceful mobile degradation
- Placeholders designed for real client data later
- Backend hooks via `/api/runway/*` stubs
